                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270111-146-off804 t18270111-146-crimeloc807"></join>. On the 2d of January, about two o'clock in the morning, the prisoner and two others came to my shop; one of them said, "What do you want for this pair of boots;" I said 5s.; but they were too small - I turned to reach another pair, and saw the prisoner and another taking something, and said, "What, are you robbing me?" they ran off - I pursued, and the prisoner dropped this pair of boots - I secured him - the others got away.</p>

               <p>
            
